# data/overrides.jsonl — MANUAL overrides, applied over the dataset by
# `atrium merge` (overlay wins). This is where hand-captured data lives:
#
#   • the facets LaunchBox doesn't carry — `color` (true=Color/false=B&W) and
#     `mouse` (true=Mouse Required/false=No Mouse);
#   • corrections to anything `atrium enrich` got wrong (e.g. a publisher name);
#   • whole records for titles `enrich` couldn't match (give id+name+app+facets).
#
# Each line is a PARTIAL record keyed by `id`; only the fields you set are
# applied. Pipeline order: harvest -> enrich (LaunchBox, fills gaps) -> merge
# (this file, wins) -> catalog/pict. Lines starting with '#' or '//' are ignored.
#
# Examples (delete/replace with real data):
# {"id":"prince-of-persia","color":true,"mouse":false}
# {"id":"dark-castle","color":false,"mouse":true}
# {"id":"glider","name":"Glider","kind":"game","year":1991,"vendor":"Casady & Greene","color":true,"mouse":true,"genre":["Arcade"],"app":"Apps/Glider/Glider"}
